TY  - JOUR
T1  - Solving Infinite-Horizon Discounted Markov Games Using a Superharmonic Least-Element Algorithm
AU  - White, D. J.
Y1  - 1993/01/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.39.1.93
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.39.1.93
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 93
EP  - 100
VL  - 39
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In this paper we present an algorithm for solving infinite-horizon discounted Markov games based upon the fact that the value function is a least element of a superharmonic set. The algorithm produces a pair of policies whose value function is within a specified error of the solution to the fixed point equation. Part of the algorithm involves solving a set of fractional programs which are replaced by equivalent linear programs.
AB  - In this paper we present an algorithm for solving infinite-horizon discounted Markov games based upon the fact that the value function is a least element of a superharmonic set. The algorithm produces a pair of policies whose value function is within a specified error of the solution to the fixed point equation. Part of the algorithm involves solving a set of fractional programs which are replaced by equivalent linear programs.
